Subtitle
16
17 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING HUMAN
18 TRAFFICKING; TO CREATE AN ENHANCED
19 PENALTY FOR RECRUITING TRAFFICKED
20 PERSONS FROM CERTAIN PLACES; AND TO
21 DECLARE AN EMERGENCY.
22
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
24
25 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 5, Chapter 18, Subchapter 1, is amended
26 to add an additional section to read as follows:
27 5-18-108. Enhanced liability — Certain conditions.
28 A person convicted of an offense under this chapter may be subject to
29 an enhanced sentence of an additional term of imprisonment not to exceed five
30 (5) years if the person recruited, enticed, or obtained a trafficked person
31 from:
32 (1) A shelter or facility operating as a residential treatment
33 center that serves runaway youth, foster children, the homeless, or other
34 persons at risk of being subjected to human trafficking, domestic violence,
35 or sexual assault;
36 (2) A correctional facility while the trafficked person was
